# Make sure all the variables with continuous values are of ‘Float’ type
df2 = df.copy()
df2['gender'] = df2['gender'].map({'Female':1,'Male':2 }).astype('float')
df2['Partner'] = df2['Partner'].map({'Yes':1,'No':0 }).astype('float')
df2['Dependents'] = df2['Dependents'].map({'Yes':1,'No':0 }).astype('float')
df2['PhoneService'] = df2['PhoneService'].map({'Yes':2,'No':1}).astype('float')
df2['MultipleLines'] = df2['MultipleLines'].map({'No phone service':0,'No':1, 'Yes':2 }).astype('float')

df2['InternetService'] = df2['InternetService'].map({'DSL':1,'Fiber optic':2,'No internet service':3}).astype('float')
df2['OnlineSecurity'] = df2['OnlineSecurity'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')
df2['OnlineBackup'] = df2['OnlineBackup'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1,'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')

df2['DeviceProtection'] = df2['DeviceProtection'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service': 2 }).astype('float')
df2['TechSupport'] = df2['TechSupport'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
df2['StreamingTV'] = df2['StreamingTV'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
df2['StreamingMovies'] = df2['StreamingMovies'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')

df2['PaperlessBilling'] = df2['PaperlessBilling'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')

df2['Contract'] = df2['Contract'].map({'Month-to-month':1, 'One year':2,'Two year':3 }).astype('float')
df2['PaymentMethod'] = df2['PaymentMethod'].map({'Electronic check':1, 'Mailed check':2,'Bank transfer (automatic)':3,'Credit card (automatic)':4 }).astype('float')

df2['Churn'] = df2['Churn'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')

#Drop the Custemer ID
df2.drop("customerID", axis=1, inplace=True)

#Change Datatype to all float
df2=df2.astype('float')
print(df2.dtypes)
print(df2.shape)

#Create draw pichart fuction for all categorical veriables

def draw_piechart(data):
    p1_color =sns.color_palette()
    fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3, ax4, ax5, ax6, ax7,ax8, ax9, ax10, ax11, ax12, ax13, ax14) = plt.subplots(ncols=14, figsize=(30,30))
    #Gender
    data.groupby('gender').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax1)
    ax1.set_ylabel('Gender', size=15)
    #Partner
    data.groupby('Partner').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax2)
    ax2.set_ylabel('Partner', size=15)
    #Dependents
    data.groupby('Dependents').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax3)
    ax3.set_ylabel('Dependents', size=15)
    #PhoneService
    data.groupby('PhoneService').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax4)
    ax4.set_ylabel('Phone Service', size=15)
    #MultipleLines
    data.groupby('MultipleLines').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax5)
    ax5.set_ylabel('MultipleLines', size=15)
    #InternetService
    data.groupby('InternetService').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax6)
    ax6.set_ylabel('Internet Service', size=15)
    #OnlineSecurity
    data.groupby('OnlineSecurity').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax7)
    ax7.set_ylabel('OnlineSecurity', size=15)
    #DeviceProtection
    data.groupby('DeviceProtection').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax8)
    ax8.set_ylabel('Device Protection', size=15)
    #TechSupport
    data.groupby('TechSupport').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax9)
    ax9.set_ylabel('TechSupport', size=15)
    #StreamingTV
    data.groupby('StreamingTV').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax10)
    ax10.set_ylabel('Streaming TV', size=15)
    #StreamingMovies
    data.groupby('StreamingMovies').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax11)
    ax11.set_ylabel('Streaming Movies', size=15)
    #Contract
    data.groupby('Contract').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax12)
    ax12.set_ylabel('Contract', size=15)
    #PaperlessBilling
    data.groupby('PaperlessBilling').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax13)
    ax13.set_ylabel('Paperless Billing', size=15)
    #PaymentMethod
    data.groupby('PaymentMethod').size().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%.0f%%', textprops={'fontsize': 16},colors=p1_color, ax=ax14)
    ax14.set_ylabel('Payment Method', size=15)
    plt.show()

Hyperparameters tuning¶

In [53]:
space={'max_depth': hp.quniform("max_depth", 3, 18, 1),
       'gamma': hp.uniform ('gamma', 1,9),
       'reg_alpha' : hp.quniform('reg_alpha', 40,180,1),
       'reg_lambda' : hp.uniform('reg_lambda', 0,1),
       'colsample_bytree' : hp.uniform('colsample_bytree', 0.5,1),
       'min_child_weight' : hp.quniform('min_child_weight', 0, 10, 1),
       'n_estimators': 180,
       'seed': 0
      }

def objective(space):
    clf=xgb.XGBClassifier(n_estimators =space['n_estimators'],
                          max_depth = int(space['max_depth']), 
                          gamma = space['gamma'],
                          reg_alpha = int(space['reg_alpha']),
                          min_child_weight=int(space['min_child_weight']),
                          colsample_bytree=int(space['colsample_bytree']))
    
    evaluation = [( X_train, y_train), ( X_test, y_test)]
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train,eval_set=evaluation, eval_metric="auc",early_stopping_rounds=10,verbose=False)
    pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, pred>0.5)
    print ("SCORE:", accuracy)
    return {'loss': -accuracy, 'status': STATUS_OK }

best_hyperparams = fmin(fn = objective, space = space, algo = tpe.suggest, max_evals = 100,trials = trials)

#File Loading Method
def load_file(file1='none', file2='none'):
    data1 = pd.read_csv(file1)
    data2 = pd.read_csv(file2)
    merge_data = pd.merge(data1, data2, on="customerID")
    return merge_data

# Data Conversion Numerical forrmate
def change_dataSetNumeric(df):
    df2=df.copy()
    df2['gender'] = df2['gender'].map({'Female':1,'Male':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['Partner'] = df2['Partner'].map({'Yes':1,'No':0 }).astype('float')
    df2['Dependents'] = df2['Dependents'].map({'Yes':1,'No':0 }).astype('float')
    df2['PhoneService'] = df2['PhoneService'].map({'Yes':2,'No':1}).astype('float')
    df2['MultipleLines'] = df2['MultipleLines'].map({'No phone service':0,'No':1, 'Yes':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['InternetService'] = df2['InternetService'].map({'DSL':1,'Fiber optic':2,'No internet service':3}).astype('float')
    df2['OnlineSecurity'] = df2['OnlineSecurity'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')
    df2['OnlineBackup'] = df2['OnlineBackup'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1,'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['DeviceProtection'] = df2['DeviceProtection'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service': 2 }).astype('float')
    df2['TechSupport'] = df2['TechSupport'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['StreamingTV'] = df2['StreamingTV'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['StreamingMovies'] = df2['StreamingMovies'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1, 'No internet service':2 }).astype('float')
    df2['PaperlessBilling'] = df2['PaperlessBilling'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')
    df2['Contract'] = df2['Contract'].map({'Month-to-month':1, 'One year':2,'Two year':3 }).astype('float')
    df2['PaymentMethod'] = df2['PaymentMethod'].map({'Electronic check':1, 'Mailed check':2,'Bank transfer (automatic)':3,'Credit card (automatic)':4 }).astype('float')
    df2['Churn'] = df2['Churn'].map({'No':0, 'Yes':1 }).astype('float')
    df2.drop("customerID", axis=1, inplace=True)
    df2['TotalCharges']=pd.to_numeric(df2['TotalCharges'], errors = 'coerce').replace(np.nan, 0)
    df2['TotalCharges']=df2['TotalCharges'].astype(float)
    df2= df2.fillna(0)
    return df2

In [66]:
def evaluate(model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)
    print("TRAINIG RESULTS: \n===============================")
    clf_report = pd.DataFrame(classification_report(y_train, y_train_pred, output_dict=True))
    print(f"CONFUSION MATRIX:\n {confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)}")
    print(f"ACCURACY SCORE:\n {accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"CLASSIFICATION REPORT:\n {clf_report}")
    print("TESTING RESULTS: \n===============================")
    clf_report = pd.DataFrame(classification_report(y_test, y_test_pred, output_dict=True))
    print(f"CONFUSION MATRIX:\n {confusion_matrix(y_test, y_test_pred)}")
    print(f"ACCURACY SCORE:\n {accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"CLASSIFICATION REPORT:\n {clf_report}")
